# Desktop UI (Electron + React)

Apply in every session (`alwaysApply: true`). Primary scope: Electron shell, preload, and renderer UI in `electron/` and `src/**/*.tsx` / `src/**/*.css`.

## 1. Electron without an app-owned HTTP server

- Treat the **renderer as the UI source of truth**: Vite in dev, static `file://` or packaged assets in production.
- **Do not** start a separate Node HTTP server in `main` just to serve the desktop UI unless there is a documented, unavoidable reason.
- Use **preload + `contextBridge`** for privileged APIs; keep the main process thin (window lifecycle, native dialogs, IPC routing).

## 2. Frameless top-level window

- Use **`frame: false`** (and related options like `titleBarStyle` / `titleBarOverlay` only where they match platform goals) on the primary `BrowserWindow` so the native chrome is hidden.
- If users need window drag/close: implement a **custom title bar** in React with `-webkit-app-region: drag` on the drag zone and `no-drag` on controls.

## 3. Startup splash (5 seconds)

- Show a **dedicated splash window or splash route** on launch with clear branding and a polished (e.g. subtle shimmer or progress) treatment.
- Show the **software version** on the splash (same value as in About; see section 8) so it matches release metadata.
- Keep the splash **visible for 5 seconds** before revealing the main window/route, unless startup hard-fails—in that case, show an error state **on or after** the splash so users are not left on a blank shell.
- Transition smoothly to the main UI (fade or cross-fade).

## 4. React and modern UI stack

- **Renderer**: React + TypeScript; keep state and side effects predictable (hooks, small components).
- Prefer **Vite**-aligned patterns already in the repo; avoid ad-hoc global script UI.

## 5. Google Material Design

- Use **Material Design 3**-aligned components (e.g. **MUI** with the MD3 theme, or another maintained Material stack the project adopts).
- Follow Material guidance for **elevation, shape, typography scale, and motion**; avoid mixing unrelated design systems on the same screen without a clear reason.

## 6. Stable `id` on UI entities

- Every **meaningful** interactive or landmark element should have a **stable `id`** (kebab-case or a consistent prefix scheme, e.g. `splash-brand`, `main-open-settings`).
- Use the same IDs in **Electron** windows where applicable (`webPreferences` / devtools debugging).
- Prefer **no duplicate `id`s** in the same document; for lists, use a **prefix + row key** pattern (`segment-row-${id}`).

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — explicit id for automation and docs
<Button id="llm-config-save" variant="contained">Save</Button>

// ❌ BAD — no stable hook for tests or support
<Button variant="contained">Save</Button>
```

## 7. Modular structure

- **Electron**: split `main` bootstrap, window factory, splash vs main window, and IPC handlers into **small modules** under `electron/` (one concern per file).
- **Renderer**: group by feature (`components/`, `core/`) with **colocated types/helpers**; avoid mega-files; extract hooks and presentational components.
- **IPC**: define channel names and payload types in a **shared module** imported by preload and main (or duplicated types with a single source of truth) to avoid string drift.

## 8. About button and software version

- Provide an **About** affordance (e.g. toolbar icon or menu entry) that opens a clear **About** surface (dialog or dedicated panel).
- The **About** section must show the **software version** (same value as `package.json` / build metadata—surface it via a single source of truth such as IPC reading app version or a Vite-injected constant).
- The **splash screen** must also display that **same software version** (e.g. under the product name or tagline) so users see it at every cold start.

## 9. Footer and copyright

- The main app layout must include a **footer** region (persistent strip at the bottom of the primary window, not obscured by scroll-only content).
- The footer must show a **copyright message** (author or legal entity and year range as appropriate for the product). Keep wording consistent with About where applicable.

## Self-check before finishing a change

- [ ] No extra desktop HTTP server unless justified.
- [ ] Primary window remains frameless per product direction.
- [ ] Splash shows for **5 seconds** before main UI unless overridden by a documented error path; splash shows **version**.
- [ ] **About** is reachable; **About** shows **version**.
- [ ] **Footer** present with **copyright** message.
- [ ] New or touched interactive UI has **stable `id`s** (include About control and footer landmarks).
- [ ] New UI uses **Material**-aligned components/tokens.
